AGENT ManifoldChecker
VERSION 1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 2
PURPOSE Measure constitutional distance from boundary at each trajectory stage
GOAL Compute per-stage distance to nearest CANNOT_MUTATE boundary
     Detect constitutional drift when distance decreases between stages
     Flag stages approaching boundary for Sovereign review
     Provide governance signal — not just where the model is but which direction it moves

RECEIVES trajectory: list, confidence: float, rival_present: bool, fields_clean: bool
EMITS distance_profile: list, min_distance: float, drift_detected: bool, flagged_stages: list
MUTATES distance_profile, drift_result
CANNOT_MUTATE boundary_constraints, distance_formula, drift_threshold, uncertainty_floor, overclaim_ceiling

CONSTRAINT Uncertainty floor is fifteen hundredths — distance is confidence minus floor
CONSTRAINT Overclaim ceiling is eighty-five hundredths — distance is ceiling minus confidence
CONSTRAINT Rival hypothesis distance is zero when absent and one when present
CONSTRAINT Field integrity distance is zero when violated and one when clean
CONSTRAINT Constitutional distance is minimum of all constraint distances
CONSTRAINT Constitutional distance is clamped between zero and one inclusive
CONSTRAINT Drift threshold is ten hundredths — CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT Drift is detected when final synthesis distance is more than threshold below mid chain distance
CONSTRAINT Stages with distance below ten hundredths are flagged for HUMAN_REVIEW

RULES
- Compute four boundary distances for each trajectory stage
- Distance from uncertainty floor: confidence minus fifteen hundredths
- Distance from overclaim ceiling: eighty-five hundredths minus confidence
- Distance from rival requirement: one when rival present, zero when absent
- Distance from field integrity: one when fields unchanged, zero when violated
- Constitutional distance is minimum of all four distances
- Clamp constitutional distance between zero and one
- Store constitutional distance on each TrajectorySample
- After computing all stage distances, check for drift
- Drift detected when final synthesis distance minus mid chain distance is less than negative threshold
- On drift detected, report direction and magnitude
- On any stage distance below threshold, add stage to flagged list
- Include constitutional distance in HMAC signing payload

PROCESS
- Receive trajectory samples, confidence, rival presence, and field integrity
- On each sample, compute four boundary distances from confidence at that stage
- Take minimum of four distances as constitutional distance for that stage
- Clamp result between zero and one
- Store constitutional distance on the sample
- After all stages computed, extract distance profile as list of floats
- Compute min distance across all stages
- Compare mid chain distance to final synthesis distance
- On final synthesis more than threshold below mid chain, set drift detected true
- Collect all stages with distance below threshold into flagged list
- Emit distance profile, min distance, drift detected, and flagged stages

CHECK
- Constitutional distance is between zero and one for every stage
- Distance profile has exactly three entries when trajectory has three samples
- Drift detection compares correct stage pair — mid chain to final synthesis
- Flagged stages list contains only stages below threshold
- Min distance equals the smallest value in distance profile
- Constitutional distance is included in HMAC signing

WHEN
- trajectory_present: activate ManifoldCheck
- drift_detected: activate DriftEscalation
- stage_flagged: activate HumanReview
- all_clear: activate NormalOperation

FAILURE
- On confidence below uncertainty floor: flag as boundary violation not just proximity
- On confidence above overclaim ceiling: flag as boundary violation not just proximity
- On missing rival hypothesis: constitutional distance is zero for that constraint
- On field integrity violated: constitutional distance is zero for that constraint

CONCEPT ManifoldCheck
PURPOSE Compute constitutional distance across all trajectory stages
APPLIES WHEN trajectory-present phase2-active
NOT WHEN trajectory-absent
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES all four boundary distances computed per stage
EFFECT each sample carries its constitutional distance for downstream consumers

CONCEPT DriftEscalation
PURPOSE Detect and flag constitutional drift between stages
APPLIES WHEN drift-detected distance-decreasing
NOT WHEN distances-stable distances-increasing
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES mid chain and final synthesis distances compared
EFFECT drift flag set for Sovereign DriftDetector integration

CONCEPT HumanReview
PURPOSE Flag stages too close to constitutional boundary
APPLIES WHEN stage-distance-below-threshold
NOT WHEN all-distances-above-threshold
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES stage distance below ten hundredths
EFFECT flagged stages reported for human review before production

OUTPUT
- distance_profile: list of floats, one per trajectory stage
- min_distance: float — closest approach to any boundary across all stages
- drift_detected: bool — true when reasoning moves toward boundary
- flagged_stages: list — stages with distance below threshold
- direction: string — toward_boundary or away_from_boundary or stable

SUCCESS
distance_accuracy: 0.30
drift_detection: 0.30
boundary_flagging: 0.20
signing_integration: 0.20
